; --------------------  
; Screen confuguration
; --------------------
;
-1		;DISPALYID of screen. You must insert this as a decimal value. Normally IDS are written in esadecimal. If you use a window the game uses ID of WorkBench Screen.
800		;WIDTH (+) of window or screen.
600		;HEIGHT	(+) of window or screen.
8		;DEPTH (+) of screen. If you use a window the game uses depth of Workbench screen.If you use non-amiga graphic devices you can not define this value becouse depth is in ID.
0		;FLAG (0-2) if set to (0) you use a screen, if you set to (1) you want a window and if you set to (2) you want a PIP window (Picture in Picture) but now only with Picasso96 and PicassoIV.
0		;FLAG (0-1) If 1 you want closeworkbench else 0 you don't want. If you use a window for game this flag is no consider. If you close workbench you get a lot of video memory.
0		;FLAG (0-1) With 1 you can have screen forcing the ratio as in 640*256 that is not 16:9,and with 0 you disable this choice.
1		;FLAG (0-1) Here you can choose if the main titles have to be done by Blitter (1) or faster by copper (0) (On Aga machines is better 0, and with a graphic board is better 1). 
800		;WIDTH (+) of the area that you want dedicate to the array of balls. With this value you can limit the size of rectangle that cointains the array of balls and limit the need of video memory. This could activate the zoom of balls. PAY ATTENTION TO THIS VALUE because if balls become smaller is more difficult to play. 
600		;HEIGHT (+) of the area that you want dedicate to the array of balls.
0		;FLAG (0-4) Here you can choose the mode of blitting. See the docs to choose method you want.
50		;PERCENTAGE (0-100) When you use the cooperative method between cpu and blitter, here you can set the percentage in blit height done by cpu. The rimanent will be done by amiga custom blitter.
5		;VALUE (+) of the the bob in graphic data array which will be used in the menu stage, the first is 1.
; ----------------
; Rotation objects	
; ----------------
1		;NUMBER (1-5) that define how many rotating objects have you. If you have only the principal pointer you must set this to 1.If you add some geares to your pointer you have to add them. 
23		;WIDTH (+) of chunky rectangle of principal pointer.
109		;HEIGHT (+) of chunky rectangle of principal pointer.
12		;X of rotation center in chunky rectangular of principal pointer.
71		;Y of rotation center in chunky rectangular of principal pointer.
14		;VALUE (1-16) of precision of rotations.
0		;VALUE (0-255) of zoom of all rotation pointers. If you use zero it has no zoom and has dimensions defined in rectangular chunky array.
1		;FLAG (0-1) If you set it to 1 you want rotation procedures to be optimized else no optimizations.
1		;PRI (0-4) of principal pointer. If you set to 0 the principal pointer has lower pri than pri of other gears the second has pri 1 the third 2 etc. Consider that if you have two gears and principal pointer to have principal pointer over geares you have to set its pri to 2. if you set this to 3 you will have pri 0.
; first gear.
51		;WIDTH (+) of graphic chunky array that define the first gear of pointer.
51		;HEIGHT (+) of graphic chunky array that define the first gear of pointer.
25		;X of rotation center of first gear in the rectangular array from 0,0.
25		;Y of rotation center of first gear in the rectangular array from 0,0.
10		;X of distance of the rotation center of this gear from the rotation center of the pointer.
10		;Y of distance of the rotation center of this gear from the rotation center of the pointer.
4294967291		;MOLTIPLIER of the variation in degree of principal pointer. If you set this to 0 this gear will not move.     
; second gear. 
49		;WIDTH (+) of graphic chunky array that define the second gear of pointer.
49		;HEIGHT (+) of graphic chunky array that define the second gear of pointer.
24		;X of rotation center of second gear in the rectangular array from 0,0.
24		;Y of rotation center of second gear in the rectangular array from 0,0.
4294967286		;X of distance of the rotation center of this gear from the rotation center of the pointer.
10		;Y of distance of the rotation center of this gear from the rotation center of the pointer.
2		;MOLTIPLIER of the variation in degree of second gear. If you set this to 0 this gear will not move.     
; -------------------
; Pointer Support
; -------------------
95		;WIDTH (+) of graphic chunky array that define the support that is under the principal poiner and substain it.
64		;HEIGHT (+) of graphic chunky array that define the support that is under the principal poiner and substain it.
48		;X of center that coincides with the rotating center of principal pointer.
17		;Y of center that coincides with the rotating center of principal pointer.
; -----
; Balls
; -----
15		;NUMBER (1-50) of balls in the graphic array.
1		;FRAMES (1-255) of anim of balls. If 1 you have only a frame.  Remember that all balls in graphic chunky file  must have the same number of anim frames.
41		;WIDTH (+) of bigger ball of set in graphic chunky array.
41		;HEIGHT (+) of bigger ball of set.
22		;WIDTH (+) of space between balls when near. If you have four tangs this value is not consider and tha game uses the WIDTH of a ball.If you have six tangs you can decide here which value to use as shift to right.
36		;HEIGHT (+) os space between balls when near.
4		;VALUE (0-31) of reduction of collision mask on the x axis. If you set this value to zero the collision respects the form of your balls defined in the graphic data.
4		;VALUE (0-31) of reduction of collision mask on the y axis.
2		;X of distance between the next ball and the ball over pointer,this is a multiplier of WIDTH of balls.
0		;Y of distance between the next ball and the ball over pointer,This is a multiplier of HEIGHT of balls.
20		;Y (+) of start position of rectangular array of balls from the top of screen/window. 
50		;Y (+) of distance from the lower end of array of balls and the ball over the pointer.
; -----------
; Controllers
; -----------
2		;VALUE in degrees of a movement of joystick and joypad to right.
2		;VALUE in degrees of a movement of joystick and joypad to left.
1		;VALUE in degrees of a movement of joystick and joypad to up.
1		;VALUE in degrees of a movement of joystick and joypad to down.
2		;VALUE in degrees of a movement of mouse to left and to right.
1		;VALUE in degrees of a movement of mouse to left and to right with right mouse button pressed.
1		;VALUE in degrees of a movement of mouse to left and to right with only right mouse button pressed.
; -----
; Fonts
; -----
32		;WIDTH (+) in pixel of the bigger letter of the large font set.The bigger letter is a form of the set and this value represent the max size.
27		;HEIGHT (+) in pixel of the bigger letter of the large font set.
16		;WIDTH (+) in pixel of the bigger letter of the small font set.
23		;HEIGHT (+) in pixel of the bigger letter of the small font set.
1		;X in pixel between two letters of large font set when written. 
2		;Y in pixel between two letters of large font set when written.
1		;X in pixel between two letters of small font set when written. 
2		;Y in pixel between two letters of small font set when written.
0		;FLAG (0-1) if you set this to 1 you don't want to have the exact distance between letters but use the value of maximum width of a letter. 
; -------
; Columns
; -------
28		;WIDTH (+) of graphic chunky array that define the left column. The game will calculate with this the right column.		
564		;HEIGHT (+) of graphic chunky array taht define the left column.
28		;WIDTH (+) of column that is out of array of balls. If it is as the WIDTH of column, the column is all out the ring.Else you can shift the column to the level.
6		;Y (+)  of start position of columns, Here you can define where columns have to be positioned from the top of screen.
; ---------------	
; Game Over Limit 
; ---------------
328		;WIDTH (+) of graphic chunky rectangle of stripe that define gameover limit.
10		;HEIGHT (+) of graphic chunky rectangle of stripe that define gameover limit.
; --------
; Aim Line
; --------
7		;WIDTH (+) of graphic chunky array that define an element of aim line.
7		;HEIGHT (+) of graphic chunky array that define an element of aim line.
1		;NUMBER (1-255) of frames in graphic chunky array of aim line.
40		;VALUE (0-255) of distance of the first element of aim line from the rotation center of pointer.
13		;VALUE (0-16) that define speed of aim line elements.If you set this to zero you will have not linear movement of aim line element.I advise you to use values from 10 to 15.
15		;VALUE (0-16) that define the distance between two elements of aim line.
28		;NUMBER (+) of elements that define the aim line.More elements you have, slower is the speed of aim line. I advise you to not ask too many aim objects and use other method as to increase the distance between elements.
13		;SPEED (0-16) of an element of aim line.An Other value.???
; ----
; Beam
; ----
328		;WIDTH (+) of grapich chunky array that define beam over balls.
20		;HEIGHT (+) of graphic chunky array that define  beam over balls.
4		;VALUE (+) of lateral movement of beam that push the balls array when it tremble.
; -----
; Timer
; -----
41		;WIDTH (+) of grapich chunky array that define a frame of timer.
41		;HEIGHT (+) of grapich chunky array that define a frame of timer.
17		;NUMBER (1-255) of frames of timer animation.
; -----
; Clock
; -----
87		;WIDTH (+) of grapich chunky array that define the clock.
87		;HEIGHT (+) of grapich chunky array that define the clock.
44		;(+) X of rotation center that coincides with the rotating center of hand, from 0,0.
44		;(+) Y of rotation center that coincides with the rotating center of hand, from 0,0.
1		;FLAG (0-2) If you set 1 you have the clock respects the second, else with 0 divides the total time in 360 equal parts. 
60		;VALUE (0-360) Here you can choose how many seconds before the time finish, the clock must have written in letters, seconds left (with 0 never, with 360 all the time). 
1		;FLAG (0-1) If you set this to 0 you will have the SMALL FONT (0) for the numbers over the clock, else with 1 you will have the BIG FONT (1).
25		;PERCENTAGE (0-100) of screen's height that define the clock's y position.
; ------------
; Clock's Hand	
; ------------
5		;WIDTH (+) of grapich chunky array that define the clock's hand.
36		;HEIGHT (+) of grapich chunky array that define the clock's hand.
3		;(+) X of rotation center of hand in  the rectangular array from 0,0.
33		;(+) Y of rotation center of hand in  the rectangular array from 0,0.
0		;VALUE (0-255) of zoom of hand. If you use zero it has no zoom and has dimensions defined in rectangular chunky array.	
; --------------
; Cpu Explosions
; --------------
13		;VALUE (1-16) that influence the cpu explosions in size.
20		;NUMBER (+) of maximum frame in cpu calculated explosion.
5		;VALUE (+) with which you can increase the frame of cpu calculated explosion.Remeber that the frame influences the dimension of the explosion.More this value begin bigger more explosion expands its width and height.
; ---------------------------
; Graphic explosion extension  
; ---------------------------
41		;WIDTH (+) of an explosion's set frame in graphic data which defines explosion's animation.
41		;HEIGHT (+) of an explosion's set frame in graphic data which defines explosion's animation.
0		;X (+) from the top left corner of pixel in a single explosion frame which coincides with the left top corner of a bob's module. With this you can center the explosion animation.
0		;Y (+) from the top left corner of pixel in a single explosion frame which coincides with the left top corner of a bob's module. With this you can center the explosion animation.
6		;FRAMES (1-255) of animation frames.
15		;NUMBER (+) of animation sequences done. If you have 8 bobs in your set and you have done an animation for each you have to set this to 8. If you do only 4 animations you will have 8 bobs using them only (bob1->fr1,bob2->fr1,bob3->fr2,bob4->fr2,..).You can do only one animation to be used by each bob, putting 1 there. 
; --------------
; Ball Movements
; --------------
10		;SPEED (1-16) of balls that you fire from your pointer.
5		;SPEED (0-255) of movement of a ball when collides to an other ball. If you set this to zero after collision the ball will go immediately to his final position.From 1 to 255 you increase the fast of tangential movement.
16		;VALUE (1-16) of speed to found collisions. If you use 16 you have the top of precision finding collisions. If you use 0 probably the game will not be able to find collisions.0 is the faster method, 16 is the slowest method but i advice you to use 15 or 16 as value.
2		;VALUE of a movement of balls from pointer. This is an other method to choose speed of balls that start from pointer.This is as the value that you add all the time to a vector that define ball direction.
8		;SPEED (1-16) of balls that fall.
8		;SPEED (0-255) of balls that fall and collide against other balls.If you set this to zero after collision the ball will go immediately to his final position.From 1 to 255 you increase the fast of tangential movement.
1		;VALUE of speed of falling balls. This is an other method to choose speed of falling balls that start from pointer.This is the value that you add all the time to a vector that define ball direction.
8		;SPEED of next ball when goes to the pointer. Represent pixels per time.
1		;FLAG (0-1) If you use 0 you have non anim of next ball when moves to pointer.If you put 1 you have anim. Mode 0 is faster.
; -----------------
; Task's priorities
; -----------------
;
; Main global tasks.
127		;TASK's PRI (-127/+127) which controls all bobs drawings. 
51		;TASK's PRI (-127/+127) which controls all objects rotations. 
40		;TASK's PRI (-127/+127) which controls all objects explosions. 
; 
; Player's tasks.
104		;TASK's PRI (-127/+127) which controls all player's sub tasks and communicates with level's tasks.
105		;TASK's PRI (-127/+127) which controls player's inputs from a remote controller (Joystick,mouse,keyboard,joypad). 
106		;TASK's PRI (-127/+127) which moves next balls to the pointer.
50		;TASK's PRI (-127/+127) which controls aim line's drawings and movements. 
35		;TASK's PRI (-127/+127) which controls the timer's drawing.
;
; Level's tasks.
101		;TASK's PRI (-127/+127) which controls all level's sub tasks and receives communications from players.
100		;TASK's PRI (-127/+127) which controls dropping bobs. 
103		;TASK's PRI (-127/+127) which asynchronously explodes level's bobs. 
102		;TASK's PRI (-127/+127) which asynchronously draws level's bobs. 
99		;TASK's PRI (-127/+127) which controls beam's tremble movements. 
30		;TASK's PRI (-127/+127) which controls score counter display. 
31		;TASK's PRI (-127/+127) which controls bob's animations. 
;* ---------------------	
;* Frames/sec of events
;* ---------------------
142		;VALUE (1-1000000) of frames in a second of ball movements from pointer.
142		;VALUE (1-1000000) of frames in a second of falling balls.
20		;VALUE (1-1000000) of frames in a second of first movement of beam.
40		;VALUE (1-1000000) of frames in a second of second movement of beam.
33		;VALUE (1-1000000) of frames in a second of drawing of all elements of aim line.
600		;VALUE (1-1000000) of frames in a second of cpu and graphic explosions.
142		;VALUE (1-1000000) of frames in a second of next ball when moves to the pointer.
500		;VALUE (1-1000000) of frames in a second of anims of balls.
